[{"category": "Escrow Service", "answer": "An escrow service refers to a contractual arrangement in which a third party (escrow agent/bank) retain and safeguard property or fund on behalf of the transaction parties and only disburses the property or fund to the beneficiary (usually the seller or service provider in the sale-purchase transaction) when all the terms and conditions of disbursement set forth in the escrow agreement are met. \nFor example, the buyer and the seller of a plot of land agree to deposit the sale-purchase amount in an escrow account opened at Wing Bank (escrow agent) to secure their transaction. Based on the escrow agreement, the bank shall only disburse the deposit amount to the seller when the seller has completed the registration of the transfer of the land to the buyer. In this case, the seller does not have to worry that the buyer refuses to pay or does not have enough money to pay for the purchased land and the buyer does not have to worry that the seller refuses to transfer the land or there is a failure in the registration process."}]

[{"category": "Escrow Service", "answer": "\u2022 Protects the buyer, seller, lender, and property owners from financial losses.\n\u2022 Minimize risk and fraud in the transaction between the parties.\n\u2022 Ensures the payment obligations are duly performed."}]

[{"category": "Escrow Service", "answer": "Wing Bank has obtained license to perform escrow services from Trust Regulator which allow the bank to provide escrow services in all types of trust in Cambodia (i.e., Public Trust, Commercial Trust, Social Trust, Financial Trust, and Individual Trust) while some banks only provide one or two types of escrow services. Therefore, when using our escrow services, you do not have to worry if your trust fund deposited with us is not recognized or protected by the law. \nMoreover, Wing Bank always cares and prioritizes the interests of its customers, and we work diligently to ensure that your money or property are safe with us, so you can be at ease when using escrow services of Wing Bank."}]

[{"category": "Escrow Service", "answer": "Wing Bank provide 5 types of escrow services in trust sector such as: 
• Public Trust: the trust fund is created for the benefit of Cambodian people in general.
• Commercial Trust: the trust fund created for the purpose of seeking profits for the benefits of the trustor or the person acknowledged by the trustor. 
• Social Trust: the trust fund is created when a trustor donates his/her property to the trustee for social benefits such as cultures, education, humanity, religion or science.
• Financial Trust: the trust fund is provided by development partners for the purpose of developing banking and micro-financial sector in Cambodia.
• Individual Trust: the trust fund is created by the trustor for the purposes of transferring assets or funds to trustee to manage and safeguard for the trustor’s own benefits or the benefits of the person determined by trustor."}]

[{"category": "Escrow Service", "answer": "Each escrow arrangement will have an escrow agreement to cover all terms and conditions of the escrow service and to be agreed and executed by the parties (the bank and the transaction parties).  \nWe only release the fund based on the conditions set forth in the escrow agreement and with your confirmation of the completion of such conditions. \nIn addition, each escrow arrangement will be registered at Trust Regulator in accordance with the trust law and related regulations in force."}]
